We had custom patches with some of the structures, when compiling under RHEL 6, the following struct was getting `redefinition` error.

Namely because in `ossl_typ.h` we had to also support RSA so we added `typedef struct rsa_oaep_params_st RSA_OAEP_PARAMS;` beside [PSS](https://github.com/openssl/openssl/blob/e04bd3433fd84e1861bf258ea37928d9845e6a86/include/openssl/ossl_typ.h#L112C1-L112C49).


```
In file included from include/openssl/x509.h:25,
                 from apps/apps.h:26,
                 from apps/opt.c:9:
include/openssl/rsa.h:303: error: redefinition of typedef 'RSA_OAEP_PARAMS'
include/openssl/ossl_typ.h:115: note: previous declaration of 'RSA_OAEP_PARAMS' was here
```

https://github.com/openssl/openssl/blob/e04bd3433fd84e1861bf258ea37928d9845e6a86/include/openssl/rsa.h#L300

Shouldn't `RSA_OEAP_PARAMS` be defined without `typedef` just like  `RSA_PSS_PARAMS`?

```
diff -urN openssl-1.1.1w-orig/include/openssl/rsa.h openssl-1.1.1w-patched/include/openssl/rsa.h
--- openssl-1.1.1w-orig/include/openssl/rsa.h	2025-09-11 02:07:53.230085491 -0700
+++ openssl-1.1.1w-patched/include/openssl/rsa.h	2025-09-12 09:52:44.914174790 -0700
@@ -294,13 +294,13 @@

 DECLARE_ASN1_FUNCTIONS(RSA_PSS_PARAMS)

-typedef struct rsa_oaep_params_st {
+struct rsa_oaep_params_st {
     X509_ALGOR *hashFunc;
     X509_ALGOR *maskGenFunc;
     X509_ALGOR *pSourceFunc;
     /* Decoded hash algorithm from maskGenFunc */
     X509_ALGOR *maskHash;
-} RSA_OAEP_PARAMS;
+};

 DECLARE_ASN1_FUNCTIONS(RSA_OAEP_PARAMS)

```

I'm trying to implement an EC encryption/decryption library using Luajit FIF. When I try to import the public key via Der format, I find that d2i_PublicKey keeps returning null, even though the public key was exported via i2d_PublicKey. However, d2i_PrivateKey and i2d_PrivateKey work fine.

OpenSSL version: 3.5.5
platform: x86-64
luajit Version: 2.0.5

